      "source": "evaluator",
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm having a weird issue with my shopify theme. on mobile the product image is overlapping the title text like it's just sitting right on top of it. i tried changing the margin but it didn't do anything. here is my css snippet for the product header:\n\n.product-header {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  padding: 20px;\n}\n\n.product-image {\n  width: 100%;\n  height: auto;\n}\n\n.product-title {\n  font-size: 24px;\n  margin-top: 10px;\n}\n\nany idea why it's overlapping on small screens?"
    },
    {
      "source": "target",
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, the overlapping issue is a common one, especially when dealing with the mobile version of your shop. It seems like your product image and title are not getting along well on smaller screens. Perhaps your product image is too tall and the title is not able to fit underneath it. You might want to consider adding a bit of padding to the product title, or even adjusting the height of the product image. \n\nHere is a little trick: try adding a `padding-top` to the `.product-title` class. This should give the title some breathing room and prevent it from overlapping with the image. You can adjust the value until you get the desired effect. \n\n```css\n.product-title {\n  font-size: 24px;\n  margin-top: 10px;\n  padding-top: 20px; /* Adjust as needed */\n}\n```\n\nRemember, sometimes it's not just about changing one thing, but rather adjusting a few things to get the perfect harmony between your product image and title. Good luck!",
